<br>
Venril(2/07): [LC, Lalliance, EB, Empire, Fama] CK, OG, KFC, CoU(1), Aargh, CdT, TSW, KCoG, CF(1), ST, HB, VFA, Ody, DR, Mara'e(1), Darksphere, Farsight, SB, Ash, HoD, Arm, CdA, ME, FK, VoE, IOM, Val(pass), GH, AM, Inc, SoO,BR/Miyabi, Enigmas, Sanctum, WM, FA, ES, ESC , Elysee , FoF , Parabellums, FireBirds, SDK, Lth, Amity, Amethyst, Nirok<br>
<br>
Please note that KGC has moved to a Limited FFA system where the tob five guilds up can all legally engage. We (KCoG) will be in the top five, and thus able to attempt VS, once he is killed eight more times.<br>
<br>
The limited FFA is pretty simple really. All five guilds/alliances in the &quot;Bracket&quot; can engage, however if more than one arrive, the higher ranking guild/alliance has priority. It is a Gentalman's Agreement, based on polite communication and respect. The intention is to speed up the rotations so more items drop. There was a ton of discussion, and this method was agreed to be a resonable balance between speeding the rotations and giving all able guilds/alliances a fair shot. It has been in place for a few weeks and seems to be working quite well.<br>
<br>
This new development also makes it all the more necessary that we be organized and ready for when our turn arrives! Let's start doing those &quot;Training Raids&quot;. I propose a few raids on Faydedar for the Druid Epic may be good practice (I'm personally ready and I'm sure there are others who are willing). What do you all think? If you all believe that would be good practice, I'd like to work with the Venril Sathir RL to set it up and really practice it like we were taking down VS!<br>
